description:
&lt;p&gt;Due to new ways of working, an opportunity has arisen for enthusiasticAdvanced Nurse Practitioner to join our ‘Brownlow family’. Do you have a particular interest in Digital Health?. Our e-Consultation service is growing rapidly so this is an exciting time to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position will include a combination of; e-Consultation, telephone consultations and acute face to face consultations. During the current Covid crisis staff have been enjoying a combination of on site and remote home working. This would be available to any new candidate after the initial 6 month induction period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Masters level study or successful RCN ANP Credentialing is essential along with non-medical prescribing. Experience in managing patients with acute presentations is essential but we are happy to support the right candidate with any skills gaps, training will be given in e- Consults.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a diverse practice population over 6 sites in the vibrant City of Liverpool and we are very proud to have attained ‘outstanding’ in our last CQC inspection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brownlow prides itself in being an exceptional employer and offers numerous staff benefits and incentives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer flexible working between 7am and 8pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Preference is for a full time staff member but consideration may be given to part time working if preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary and Annual leave is in line with Agenda for Change . Band 8a /7 depending on qualifications and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 25th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like an informal chat or more information please contact Maria.Sullivan@livgp.nhs.uk or Joanne.David@livgp.nhs.uk &lt;/p&gt;
